<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" ng-app="ErrorReporter">
<head>
    <title>Dyspro Error Reporter</title>

    <script src="js/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/angular.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/bootstrap.min.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/site.css"/>

</head>
<body ng-controller="ErrorReporterController">

<nav class="navbar navbar-default" role="navigation">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="navbar-header">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Dyspro</a>
            <p class="navbar-text">/ Error Reporter</p>
        </div>
        <form class="navbar-form navbar-right col-md-3" role="form" method="post">
            <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Email" class="form-control" name="LoginEmail" required>
                <input type="password" placeholder="Password" class="form-control" name="LoginPassword" required>
                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Sign in</button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="container" role="main">
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <h1>Simple Error Reporting</h1>
        <p>The Dyspro Error Reporter moves exception reporting outside of your application environments.  This
        gives you power over statistical analysis of the health of your system.</p>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>